    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: 0.4.4\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? no\r\n- Operating system/version: Manjaro Linux\r\n- Terminal name/version: kitty 0.18.3\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u NORC\r\n:set signcolumn=yes:1\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nTwo columns are used, even though `signcolumn` is set to `1`.\r\n![2020-10-16-064928_93x73_scrot](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46303212/96216636-11dfa780-0f81-11eb-902c-7668c417131c.png)\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nOne column is used regardless of whether marker can fit into one column.\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\nAs of right now, values passed to `signcolumn` are multiples of 2 (this means that setting it to 1 yields 2 real columns, 2 yields 4 real columns etc.), which is not an obvious behavior. If so, the accepted values would be expected to be 2, 4, 6 etc. This behavior is not documented in `:h 'signcolumn'`.\r\n\r\n### Suggestion\r\nIdeal solution would be to make `signcolumn` yield 1 column given number 1.\r\nIf this is rejected, or as temporary measure, document that this option produces multiples of two of the given number.\r\n\r\n### Previous work\r\nAbandoned work in this area: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/9788\r\nALE tracking issue: https://github.com/dense-analysis/ale/issues/1015\r\n`signcolumn` implementation tracking issue: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/990\r\n`signcolumn` implementation: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/36762a00a8010c5e14ad4347ab8287d1e8e7e064",
